docs.abstract: Editorial criticizes North Carolina Gov Pat McCrory for offering to hold special legislative session to repeal discriminatory law that prevents transgender people from using toilets that match their gender identity, but only if city of Charlotte revokes its anti-discrimination ordinance; praises Charlotte Mayor Jennifer Roberts for refusing to give in; contends McCrory and Republican lawmakers are sole reason North Carolina faces loss of hundreds of jobs and millions of dollars as businesses and sports organizations walk away from bigotry.

headline.main: North Carolina Pays a Price for Bigotry
